<$fill $name="body">

!! Three-layer mixin system

* ''rrc0.* (Core/Model)'' — element list, type mapping, visibility, view dispatch, click dispatch, CSS classes
** `rrc0.elems()` — returns element list
** `rrc0.elem-type(element)` — maps element to type code
** `rrc0.elem-visible(element)` — visibility filter
** `rrc0.elem-view(element)` — rendering dispatch
** `rrc0.elem-clicked(element)` — click handler dispatch
** `rrc0.elem-add-class(element)` — CSS class dispatch

* ''rrc1.* (Behavior)'' — state handling, selection, type-specific handlers
** State functions, sync functions, type-specific handlers
** Delegation pattern: check `rrc1.<op>:<type>`, fallback to `rrc1.<op>`, use default

!! Facade components

|!Facade |!Parameters |!Key slots |!Rendering |
|`pills` |elements, selection, filterable, sync-tiddler, sync-field, state, instid |view, on-select |Transcludes `core/menu` |
|`vtabs` |elements, type-fn, state, instid, visible-types, default-collapsed, lnk-navigate |view-sec, view-act, view-pop, view-lnk, view-sco, view-spa, view (fallback) |Inlines render loop |

!! Core renderer

`core/menu.tid`: generic renderer with `$eventcatcher` catching clicks on `.rrc-elem`, dispatching to `rrc0.elem-clicked`.

!! Why vtabs inlines the render loop

`$slot` inside `\procedure` doesn't find `$fill` from outer `$transclude $tiddler=`. vtabs puts `$slot` at body level with `<%if%>` type branching as a workaround. pills works because it transcludes `core/menu` (intermediate tiddler boundary).

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="warning">
